title: Prep roundup: Herbie Wright leads Prosser to win on New Years Eve | Prep Sports | yakimaherald.com
text:
KISSIMEE, Fla. — The end of 2025 marked the end of the Prosser girls basketball team's Florida trip, and Herbie Wright made sure both ended on a positive note.
Wright poured in a game-high 27 points on Wednesday as she led the Mustangs to a 56-33 win over Avon Lake of Ohio to claim third place in the KSA Holiday Tournament's Red Bracket at the Gaylord Palms Resort.
Wright nearly outscored the Shoremen by herself, but Amelia Chapman added nine points and Lailah Carter chipped in eight.
Prosser (8-2) will return home and resume CWAC play against Selah on Tuesday.

CLARKSTON 65, ELLENSBURG 61: At Lewis-Clark State, Bella Standish scored 25 points as the Bulldogs fell in the title game of the Avista Holiday Tournament. Standish, who surpasses 1,000 career points on Monday, was named to the all-tournament team.
Ellensburg (6-3) will resume CWAC play at home against Quincy on Friday.
Ellensburg vs. Clarkston at Lewis-Clark State, 2:30 p.m.

BOYS BASKETBALL
NONLEAGUE
CLARKSTON 56, ELLENSBURG 44: At Lewis-Clark State, Will Bennett scored 18 points and was named to the Avista Tournament's all-tournament team after the Bulldogs' loss. Ellensburg (3-6) will resume CWAC play on Friday at home against Quincy.
In other boys action Wednesday, Prosser fell 53-33 to Shaker (N.Y.) on the final day of the KSA Holiday Tournament at Gaylord Palms Resort in Kissimmee, Fla.
